Just a heads up.

    for(int i =0; i &lt; arithmetic_expression.size() ; ++i){

        ...

        arithmetic_expression.pop();
    }

is logically incorrect. When you pop the top of the stack, size of the stack goes down by 1. By incrementing `i` and comparing it with the size of the stack, you will end up ignoring half of the stack. You can fix that by using:

    // There is no need for i
    for ( ; arithmetic_expression.size() &gt; 0; arithmetic_expression.pop()) {

       ...

    }

